  <!-- History -->
<section class="py-16 bg-secondary-100">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-secondary-900">Our Journey</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-secondary-800 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        A timeline of our evolution and achievements.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ol class="relative border-s border-secondary-500 dark:border-secondary-800 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <li class="mb-10 ms-4">
        <div class="absolute w-3 h-3 bg-secondary-800 rounded-full mt-1.5 -start-1.5 border border-white dark:border-secondary-900"></div>
        <time class="mb-1 text-sm font-normal leading-none text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-700 uppercase">Aug. - Nov. 2022</time>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-secondary-900">At a  Crossroads</h3>
        <p class="text-base font-normal text-secondary-800 dark:text-secondary-800">
          Our previous head coach, Gail Drake, and all other mentors from ILITE departed. In the months that followed, our students explored various options. We considered a "training season" to regroup or forming an FTC team. During this period, several students who had been part of ILITE chose to join other teams such as 8592 Newton<sup>2</sup>.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li class="mb-10 ms-4">
        <div class="absolute w-3 h-3 bg-secondary-800 rounded-full mt-1.5 -start-1.5 border border-white dark:border-secondary-900"></div>
        <time class="mb-1 text-sm font-normal leading-none text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-700 uppercase">Nov. 2022</time>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-secondary-900">Rebuilding with Purpose</h3>
        <p class="text-base font-normal text-secondary-800 dark:text-secondary-800">
          Despite the departures, seven committed members chose to stay and rebuild. We were incredibly fortunate to welcome <a target="_blank" rel="noopenner noreferrer" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/lea-may-28385a256" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 hover:underline">Mrs. May</a> as our new head coach, who brought with her a wealth of experience and her husband, Mr. May, a talented software engineer. This marked the true beginning of Comet Robotics.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li class="mb-10 ms-4">
        <div class="absolute w-3 h-3 bg-secondary-800 rounded-full mt-1.5 -start-1.5 border border-white dark:border-secondary-900"></div>
        <time class="mb-1 text-sm font-normal leading-none text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-700 uppercase">2023 Season</time>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-secondary-900">Forging Our Own Identity</h3>
        <p class="text-base font-normal text-secondary-800 dark:text-secondary-800">
          The 2023 season was filled with challenges, but it was also a period where we truly distinguished ourselves. We focused on cultivating a kind, respectful, and fun attitude. Our efforts were recognized at our second competition in Alexandria, Virginia, where we proudly won the Team Spirit Award.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li class="mb-10 ms-4">
        <div class="absolute w-3 h-3 bg-secondary-800 rounded-full mt-1.5 -start-1.5 border border-white dark:border-secondary-900"></div>
        <time class="mb-1 text-sm font-normal leading-none text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-700 uppercase">2024 Season</time>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-secondary-900">Soaring with Outreach and Recognition</h3>
        <p class="text-base font-normal text-secondary-800 dark:text-secondary-800">
          Our dedicated work in the community led us to win the Engineering Inspiration Award at our Blacksburg event. We continued our winning streak at the Alexandria event, once again securing the Team Spirit Award. Our hard work culminated in our first-ever trip to Districts, where we competed for the Engineering Inspiration Award, a significant milestone for our growing team.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li class="mb-10 ms-4">
        <div class="absolute w-3 h-3 bg-secondary-800 rounded-full mt-1.5 -start-1.5 border border-white dark:border-secondary-900"></div>
        <time class="mb-1 text-sm font-normal leading-none text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-700 uppercase">2024 Offseason</time>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-secondary-900">First Offseason Competitions & Custom Build</h3>
        <p class="text-base font-normal text-secondary-800 dark:text-secondary-800">
          The 2024 offseason marked our first attendance at off-season competitions and our debut building a robot from scratch, moving beyond kitbots. Our design, a modified clone of 9496 LYNK's LATCH, competed at the Chesapeake Robotics Icebreaker and Battle o' Baltimore. At BoB, we achieved a qualification rank of 6 and were proud to captain Alliance 6. Although it was just an offseason event, it was the first time we had ever captained an alliance.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li class="ms-4">
        <div class="absolute w-3 h-3 bg-secondary-800 rounded-full mt-1.5 -start-1.5 border border-white dark:border-secondary-900"></div>
        <time class="mb-1 text-sm font-normal leading-none text-secondary-700 dark:text-secondary-700 uppercase">2025 Season</time>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-secondary-900 dark:text-secondary-900">Fully CADed Robot & District Qualification</h3>
        <p class="text-base font-normal text-secondary-800 dark:text-secondary-800">
          The 2025 season saw us fully CAD our own robot for the first time, an 'Algae-focused shooter bot.' Our robot's performance also earned us our first-ever qualification for Districts.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>
  
